Echinopla wardi sp. n. is similar to Echinopla australis Forel, 1901 from Australia, but this species has yellow legs and funiculus, relatively long pilosity, and pronotal width distinctly smaller than head width. Images of Echinopla australis are presented by Antweb (2015) . According to the original description (
Andre 1892
), Echinopla rugosa Andre , 1892 from Borneo has similar structures of mesosoma and petiole, but differs by uniformly black colour with bronze shimmer and slightly smaller size. Unfortunately the holotype depository of this enigmatic species is unknown and no further specimen has become known. See also notes for Echinopla madli sp. n. and Echinopla brevisetosa sp. n.
